result.execSummary:
The defendant James Baggett was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500) [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant James Baggett in court, in custody, with attorney M. Elizabeth Weathers.    District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court conducts plea colloquy. State has offer to dismiss and read-in Counts #1 and #2 if defendant pleads Guilty to Count #3. Defendant pleads guilty to Count # 3. Court finds defendant guilty of Count #3. Counts #1 and #2 will be dismissed and read-in. State makes recommendations. Attorney Weathers makes statements. Defendant makes statements.

The Court Orders the Following to Count #3:

90 Days Jail. (Credit - 90 days).  TIME SERVED.

COSTS: $253.00

DNA Surcharge: $200.00

DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 
 
Total costs/fine/forfeiture: in lieu of payments, defendant to serve 20 days Jail. (Credit - 20 days.) TIME SERVED. Consecutive to 90 day sentence.

Court reinstates defendant's cash bail previously ordered forfeited.

RESTITUTION: $107.38 to be paid to Waukesha County District Attorney's Office. Cash bail posted to be applied; remaining $7.38 to be paid within 90 days. Failure to pay;  the Court orders the defendant to serve 2 days in Waukesha County Jail.
